This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: No Contact Order signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3. No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with AAB (DOB: 12/13/1978) or JDJ (DOB: 09/16/1998). Court advised Defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Jamaal Tyrell Jackson appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Andrew Joel Golden appeared by video for Jamaal Tyrell Jackson.  Prosecuting attorney Abby Rockendorf appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant is advised that due to the intake calendar of the week, this case has been re-assigned to Judge Skwierawski, Branch 41. Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for December 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
